commit.message:
Switch to sphinxcontrib-programoutput

*Much* cleaner!

Switch to sphinx-autorun

Have to use the Python console style for now, for cross-platform
compat (currently the shell execution is hardcoded to bash).

Also, it looks like there's no way to add 'setup' code to run,
so for now the preamble with runpy &c. seems to be unavoidable.

Convert docs builds to matrix

No reason to repeat the nearly identical job content

Add Sphinx doctests to Travis

Constrain pytest doctests to just README, which Sphinx can't
easily reach.

Only installing docs requirements for 3.7 b/c Sphinx>=2
doesn't support 3.4.

Add draft method inheritance printout

Still have to manually update based on doctest results,
but at least it's easy to keep it fresh/accurate -- just
copy/paste from the failed doctest output.

commit.message:
Add graphviz install

Needed in order for the inheritance diagram not to raise a
warning-turned-error.

Try aliasing _io members

The inheritance diagram appears to be inserting a Sphinx reference
to _io.BytesIO and other members of _io, which do not exist in the
Python docs objects.inv.

Hopefully aliasing _io.foo --> io.foo will change
how those references are constructed...

Revise graphviz/inheritance_diagram settings

Also add constraint to importlib_metadata version, to try to fix
the sudden 3.8-dev error in Travis.
Increase heap size to 20MB
Switch to get-pip.py
Try ensurepip & pip install of pytest

CI: Add MicroPython to Azure

Relates to #81.

RTD: Require Sphinx>=2

1.8.5 is giving an inexplicable 'contents.rst not found' error,
both locally and on RTD. 2.2.0 should hopefully make things
happy again.
